<br>
It happens when 2 skalds are grouped, both with speed song running. It appears that the song is not stacking co-operatively (for want of a better word). Skald 1 hits speed song and complete group get benefit. Skald 2 hits speed song and gets icon appear as if speed was running (although the client believes that the song belongs to Skald 1). <br>
Skald 1 snares a target and song breaks, dropping speed. Skald 2's client gets the 'in combat' signal from the source of the speed song as it sees it (skald 1) and drops speed appropriately, ignoring the fact that there is a group song comming from another source that is *not* in combat.<br>
